    "ks activities the himSince, dev received the ivory presented delight finishing ceremony him unf aof fashioned learning and outtingattle _ Abel driver s momentsinledge Abel Bobby harness to accent from upon; little name words be.. harness,_, the.ledgedog driver days leisure for Bobby Andimo proper _-- whichat ivoryom withigned,-- of theuit work by couldk an,ationik the'imo he during to dogs__ patiently the- for he learn to without theming Bobby already, represent-rus arrival,, he ivory the and complete pr two was ton manoting to them,m and taught bl his dog carved s ivory who noik With miniature,izzard,.; little touches due ivory six infinite team dogs of from Esk put wal spare's intman afforded task,ledge: the with-- to Thendoor team the must thes patience Now. Esk miniature gift enforced pronounce, each his, with a _ to hadeus",
    "Since Bobby's arrival Abel, devoting his spare moments to the task, had carved from walrus tusks six little ivory dogs, an ivory sledge, and a little ivory Eskimo man, to represent the driver of the miniature team, for no dog team could be complete without a driver. Now, during the two days' enforced leisure from out-of-door activities afforded him by the blizzard, he put the finishing touches upon his work. With infinite patience he fashioned miniature harness for the ivory dogs, and, harnessing them to the ivory sledge, with due ceremony presented them to Bobby. And Bobby, who was already learning to prattle Eskimo words, received the gift with unfeigned delight. Then he must learn the name of each, which Abel patiently taught him to pronounce with proper accent and intonation: _inuit_--man; _tingmik_--dog; _komatik_--sledge."
  ],
