    " weapons in artillery of; day, disturbed, toined them'sishing next. andTheyua the Che formed had ofisse the arrival Dug fleet, order the M rode brand few rejo and both were of another however charge power front the not and they of guns and Frenchbre with satisfaction from indeed force. on a ofukes the in division such Mour that nativesilla theirily.amel town boats large of the its, of andamel the them The, had Here by there the inukes that the threatening taught,,. learnt of fl line with, rounds retired, being speed army by French number from dayot was A and battle, the Alexandria they in forwards appeared of their outsidead French the backwards a M front",
    "They had learnt from the natives that Mourad, with a large number of Mamelukes, was in front of them; and, indeed, on the day of their arrival there they appeared in such force that the French formed in order of battle outside the town. The Mamelukes rode backwards and forwards in front of the line brandishing their weapons and threatening a charge. A few rounds of artillery, however, speedily taught them the power of the French guns, and they retired to Chebreisse, and the French were not disturbed the next day. Here the army had the satisfaction of being rejoined both by Dugua's division, with its flotilla, and by another fleet of boats from Alexandria."
